ce:section.ce:para:
The purified Aloe vera gel after filtration and centrifugation was subjected to GCMS analysis to quantify the major constituents present in the extract (Fig. 6
                         and Table 2
                        ). Aloe-emodin and aloin have displayed properties that serve for wound healing and angiogenetic properties along with anti-inflammatory effects. Hence the presences of such compounds were confirmed through this study. Emodin and aloin were detected from the available list of compounds present in the mixture at retention times of 24.9–25.89 (Malmir et al., 2020).

The natural CQDs and the aloe- emodin conjugated CQDs were tested for their anti- microbial properties against both the Gram positive and negative strains (Fig. 7
                         and Table 3
                        ). The diameter of the inhibition zones were measured to reveal the antagonistic property of both the independent and the conjugated CQDs. Gram negative strain, E. coli seemed to respond better to the CQDs than the positive strains as a whole. The maximum zone of inhibition was noticed to be 19 mm for the conjugated CQDs and 17 mm were observed for the CQDs towards the same strain. Ultra-small CQDs are known to penetrate the bacterial cells and can destroy them due to their ROS generation properties. The anti- bactericidal action of aloe- emodin has favored the penetrability and cellular destruction. This might be due to the better penetration and larger pore sizes of the Gram negative strain (Arumugham et al., 2020; Li et al., 2016)
